    "body": "## Summary\n\nAdd a fused CUDA kernel (`trtllm::fused_cat_fp8`) that combines BF16 tensor concatenation and FP8 E4M3 1×128 quantization into a single kernel launch. This replaces the sequential `cat → fp8_quantize_1x128` path in the DSA indexer's `_prep_q_or_k()`, reducing per-call kernel launches from 2+ down to 1.\n\n### Changes\n- **New CUDA kernel** (`fusedCatFp8.cu/h`): 1 warp (32 threads) per row, 8 rows per block. Vectorized 8-byte `int2` loads for BF16 inputs, 4-byte `uint32_t` stores for FP8 outputs. Per-row FP8 quantization with warp-reduced amax.\n- **Template specialization** on `UseUe8m0`: eliminates runtime branching for scale format. UE8M0 path uses IEEE 754 bit manipulation instead of `ceilf(log2f(...))` + `exp2f(...)`. Hardware `rcp.approx.ftz` for fast reciprocal.\n- **Non-contiguous input support**: accepts row strides directly, handling `torch.split()` views without a prior `.contiguous()` copy.\n- **Torch op registration**: registered via `TORCH_LIBRARY_FRAGMENT` with fake tensor support for `torch.compile`.\n- **DSA integration** (`dsa.py`): `_prep_q_or_k()` now calls the single fused op, removing imports for `maybe_compiled_cat` and `fp8_utils`.\n- **`rotate_activation` restored** as a standalone utility in `dsa.py` for future use (not called in the current code path).\n\n### Files\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `cpp/tensorrt_llm/kernels/fusedCatFp8.cu` | Fused CUDA kernel implementation |\n| `cpp/tensorrt_llm/kernels/fusedCatFp8.h` | Kernel header with API docs |\n| `cpp/tensorrt_llm/thop/fusedCatFp8Op.cpp` | Torch op binding (TORCH_LIBRARY_FRAGMENT) |\n| `cpp/tensorrt_llm/thop/CMakeLists.txt` | Build integration |\n| `tensorrt_llm/_torch/attention_backend/sparse/dsa.py` | Use fused op in `_prep_q_or_k()` |\n| `tensorrt_llm/_torch/custom_ops/cpp_custom_ops.py` | Fake tensor registration for compile |\n| `tests/unittest/_torch/thop/serial/test_fused_cat_fp8.py` | Comprehensive unit tests |\n\n## Test plan\n- [x] Unit test: `tests/unittest/_torch/thop/serial/test_fused_cat_fp8.py` — contiguous, non-contiguous, odd M values, UE8M0 and standard scale formats, stride alignment validation\n- [x] Integration: DeepSeek-V3/R1 decode serving with fused path\n- [x] CI: `/bot run`",
